          <div id="container1">
            <h3>Question: What is Sched?</h3>
            <p><b>Answer:</b></p>
            <p>Sched is a social-networking platform focused on connecting peoples different training schedules.
              It makes it easier for everyone to see others schedule in one place, rather then to ask each person
              individually.</p>
          </div>

          <div id="container2">
            <h3>Question: Who are we?</h3>
            <p><b>Answer:</b></p>
            <p>The creator of Sched is <a href="https://se.linkedin.com/in/felix-wetell-15a19b94">Felix Wetell</a> and
              <a href="https://se.linkedin.com/in/sandro-caputo-093a92110">Sandro Caputo.</a>
              We are two student in the last year of swedish high school reading Technology Programme with
              Specialization in Information and Media Communication.</p>
          </div>

          <div id="container3">
            <h3>Question: Why are we doing this?</h3>
            <p><b>Answer:</b></p>
            <p>Sched is our graduation work and also a personal project for us.
              We wanted to make a platform to make it less hard to find people to train with.</p>
          </div>

          <div id="container4">
            <h3>Question: How do Sched work?</h3>
            <p><b>Answer:</b></p>
            <p>Sched works by letting users and their training schedule to the site and follow other users to see theirs.</p>
          </div>

          <div id="container5">
            <h3>Question: Why should I use Sched?</h3>
            <p><b>Answer:</b></p>
            <p>If you have ever experienced difficulty to get a clear answer when you ask your friends when and where
              they are going to train, then this is the site for you.
              Sched lets you share your schedule to users that follows and too see other followed users schedule.</p>
          </div>

          <div id="container6">
            <h3>Question: How have we created this?</h3>
            <p><b>Answer:</b></p>
            <p>Sched is coded using several differnet programming languages, Ruby, JavaScript, HTML5, CSS3 and SQLite3
              but also with the framework Sinatra.
              Togehter have we coded the site in both back-end and front-end from the ground. We shared te work between
              use, Sandro having the focus on back-end with Ruby, Sinatra and SQLite3.
              Felix focus was to work on the front-end with HTML5, CSS3 and JavaScript.</p>
          </div>

          <div id="container7">
            <h3>Question: How do I add an activity?</h3>
            <p><b>Answer:</b></p>
            <p>First you have to log in.</p>
            <p>When logged in you look to the right of the screen where you can see the Event header.
              Under that header, there are some options. Fill them in with information as accurate as your event details
              and click "Submit".</p>
            <p>When this is done, the event should appear on the left under "Events on selected day" at the day you set
              it too.
              If not, reload the page and click on the chosen day. </p>
          </div>

